{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"0b4eddd8-c406-43fc-a9b3-897bdd40486f","title":"Morphic for the web","desc":null,"updated":1633673175,"created":1616113980165,"custom":{},"fname":"projects.morphic","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"de154927e7f16176a425f4f3b1b9a2ad","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"projects.morphic","id":"0b4eddd8-c406-43fc-a9b3-897bdd40486f","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"theory.interaction-semantics","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":97,"offset":311},"end":{"line":4,"column":129,"offset":343},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"theory.interaction-semantics"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"projects.morphic","id":"0b4eddd8-c406-43fc-a9b3-897bdd40486f","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"theory.bricolage","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":58,"offset":478},"end":{"line":7,"column":78,"offset":498},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"theory.bricolage"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"projects.morphic","id":"0b4eddd8-c406-43fc-a9b3-897bdd40486f","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"theory.figma-for-x","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":127,"offset":775},"end":{"line":13,"column":149,"offset":797},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"theory.figma-for-x"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"projects.morphic","id":"0b4eddd8-c406-43fc-a9b3-897bdd40486f","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"theory.metaballs","alias":"metaball","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":36,"offset":835},"end":{"line":15,"column":65,"offset":864},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"theory.metaballs"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"projects.morphic","id":"0b4eddd8-c406-43fc-a9b3-897bdd40486f","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"projects.linear-algebra-spreadsheet","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":82,"offset":953},"end":{"line":17,"column":121,"offset":992},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"projects.linear-algebra-spreadsheet"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"projects.morphic","id":"0b4eddd8-c406-43fc-a9b3-897bdd40486f","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"projects.system-archaeology","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":10,"offset":2189},"end":{"line":35,"column":41,"offset":2220},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"projects.system-archaeology"}}],"anchors":{},"children":[],"parent":"5988f8ec-c945-458a-8309-9f318af16602","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"morphic-for-the-web\">Morphic for the web<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#morphic-for-the-web\"></a></h1>\n<p>I was astonished by the mode of interacting in Self's <a href=\"https://handbook.selflanguage.org/2017.1/morphic.html\">Morphic environment</a>, demonstrated in <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ox5P7QyL774\">Self: The Movie;</a>.</p>\n<p>You create a green, empty \"morph\" on a 2D plane, and then right-click it to open a context menu <a href=\"/inquiry/notes/bff6ee82-45d7-4702-bb59-542b05920ae9\">How do you create an interaction semantics?</a>, where you can assign behavior:\n<img src=\"/inquiry/assets/images/2021-03-18-20-35-15.png\"></p>\n<p>You can decompose any piece of content and rearrange it, <a href=\"/inquiry/notes/4a69ebf0-4af7-4e56-b4c5-5e9dbd633d32\">Bricolage</a>-style.</p>\n<p>It's even realtime multiplayer in the local network!</p>\n<p><img src=\"/inquiry/assets/images/2021-03-18-20-39-31.png\"><img src=\"/inquiry/assets/images/2021-03-18-20-39-32.png\"></p>\n<p>What does this kind of environment look like if implemented today? GToolkit is cool. SqueakJS is cool. Figma for Smalltalk!? (<a href=\"/inquiry/notes/f2d1c8a1-5bb9-4cd6-816c-afe6ea86935a\">Figma for X</a>)</p>\n<p>What if the morphs were more jelly/<a href=\"/inquiry/notes/8696586c-2cfc-47a2-b483-e1e6be539a20\">metaball</a>-like?</p>\n<p>Programming in 2D is only making a comeback recently (eg some of the projects in <a href=\"/inquiry/notes/06ea3d39-0b83-4052-86f2-f1e82499b266\">Linear Algebra as Spreadsheet</a> like Paul Shen's)</p>\n<p><img src=\"/inquiry/assets/images/2021-03-18-20-41-44.png\"></p>\n<p>(<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CCx6Nj_Hr1g\">Systems with JT</a>. BTW <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/giard321/featured\">his channel</a> has some great \"OS Let's Plays\")</p>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">also turns me off in many HCI prototypes I've seen, and in the old-school Smalltalk browser UI. feels very buttons and menus world, very un-wiggly</p>â€” Omar Rizwan (@rsnous) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/rsnous/status/1372694522669330437?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">March 18, 2021</a></blockquote> <script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n<p><img src=\"/inquiry/assets/images/vaporize.gif\"></p>\n<p>Another system by Randall Smith is <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I9LZ6TnSP40\">Alternate Reality Kit</a></p>\n<p>Also Dan Ingalls' <a href=\"https://lively-web.org/\">Lively-Web</a>, which isn't quite as performant or rich as I'd want - similar to Omar's sentiment on Smalltalk above.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/codefrau\">Vanessa Freudenberg</a>/Croquet Team is a good person to talk to about this.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://haijunxia.ucsd.edu/assets/projects/2016_OOD/object-oriented%20drawing.pdf\">Object Oriented Drawing</a></p>\n<p>Related: <a href=\"/inquiry/notes/90f43805-4858-4d25-8f51-6dec373f6b2f\">System Archaeology Seminar</a></p>","noteIndex":{"id":"940ad93a-2b54-497e-ab18-335879950834","title":"Max's Inquiry","updated":1616115341623,"modified":"2022-08-26T16:46:41.000Z","desc":null,"custom":{"modified":"2022-08-26T16:46:41.000Z","nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"7936220386f369ace243d8e835153790","created":1695797153867,"links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"940ad93a-2b54-497e-ab18-335879950834","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"projects.linear-algebra-spreadsheet","alias":"Linear algebra as spreadsheet","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":3,"offset":949},"end":{"line":16,"column":72,"offset":1018},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"projects.linear-algebra-spreadsheet"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"940ad93a-2b54-497e-ab18-335879950834","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"rethinking-media.microworld-languages","alias":"Domain learning for computational microworlds","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":3,"offset":1021},"end":{"line":17,"column":90,"offset":1108},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"rethinking-media.microworld-languages"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"940ad93a-2b54-497e-ab18-335879950834","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"projects.linux-desktop","alias":"Linux DE prototyping","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":3,"offset":1111},"end":{"line":18,"column":50,"offset":1158},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"projects.linux-desktop"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"940ad93a-2b54-497e-ab18-335879950834","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"projects.system-archaeology","alias":"System Archaeology","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":3,"offset":1161},"end":{"line":19,"column":53,"offset":1211},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"projects.system-archaeology"}}],"anchors":{"guide":{"type":"header","text":"Guide","value":"guide","line":19,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["2e6e45b5-be90-4ef3-8720-6e52ce04cb9a","5988f8ec-c945-458a-8309-9f318af16602","86c66ea6-63bc-4711-8eff-13bb9260db4f","d8a51d81-83c8-45b4-84fa-9b55dce793ac"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\nThis is [Max Krieger](https://a9.io)'s \"inquiry\" page. I guess it's like a [Digital Garden](https://github.com/MaggieAppleton/digital-gardeners). But I'm not trying to upload my Second Brain to it. Just want to share some half-baked ideas. One source of inspiration for this was Kevin Lynagh's [\"Collaboration ideas\"](https://kevinlynagh.com/ideas/). See also Sharif Shameem's [\"Questions\"](https://sharif.io/questions/).\n\nIt was made with [Dendron](https://dendron.so).\n\nTake everything I write here (well, everywhere) with a grain of salt. That said I'm always happy to talk about anything on here.\n\nThe pages definitely don't adhere to [Andy's Evergreen Notes](https://notes.andymatuschak.org/z4SDCZQeRo4xFEQ8H4qrSqd68ucpgE6LU155C) pattern, I hope one day they do.\n\nFeel free to add [a PR or issue to the repo](https://github.com/maxkrieger/inquiry) to discuss any of these in public!\n\n## Guide\n\nHere are some of my favorite/extensive pages:\n\n- [[Linear algebra as spreadsheet|projects.linear-algebra-spreadsheet]]\n- [[Domain learning for computational microworlds|rethinking-media.microworld-languages]]\n- [[Linux DE prototyping|projects.linux-desktop]]\n- [[System Archaeology|projects.system-archaeology]]\n\n---\n\n![](/assets/images/2021-03-18-20-55-10.png)\n\n[El Lissitzky, The Constructor (self-portrait, 1924)](https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:El_Lissitzky_The_Constructor,_self-portrait,_gelatin_silver_print,_107%C3%97118_mm,_1924_London,_Victoria_and_Albert_Museum,_Inv._PH142-1985.jpg)\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":false,"leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true,"fuzzThreshold":0.2,"vaultSelectionModeOnCreate":"smart"}},"insertNote":{"initialValue":"templates"},"insertNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"none","enableMultiSelect":false},"insertNoteIndex":{"enableMarker":false},"randomNote":{},"copyNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"title"},"templateHierarchy":"template"},"workspace":{"dendronVersion":"0.87.0","vaults":[{"fsPath":"vault"}],"journal":{"dailyDomain":"daily","name":"journal","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd","addBehavior":"childOfDomain"},"scratch":{"name":"scratch","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd.HHmmss","addBehavior":"asOwnDomain"},"graph":{"zoomSpeed":1